## Acknowledgements

The first IUCN Red List assessment of South African spiders was conducted between 2016 and 2019, as a collaborative project between the South African National Biodiversity Institute (SANBI), the Agricultural Research Council, the University of the Free State, National Museum Bloemfontein, and the University of Venda (formerly University of Limpopo) and the National Re-search Foundation (NRF) for generously funding and support. South African National Parks and E. Oppenheimer & Son support and provide opportunities to collect in the parks and reserves and the provincial conservation agencies for collecting permits.

All the field workers, museum staff and other members contributing to the completion of the assessment are acknowledged for their contributions (@tbl-2).

